vCard

T:
                        +1 212 548 7012F:
                        +1 212 715 23151345 Avenue of the Americas7th FloorNew York, NY 10105-0106













Served as national counsel for major companies in defense of thousands of asbestos-related claims throughout the country. Handled cases directly in the NYCAL, managed nationwide local counsel network, developed and implemented strategies for handling of cases, engaged in settlement negotiations with key plaintiff counsel throughout the U.S. and address other related issues such as indemnification and insurance coverage disputes.
Handled litigation defending mass tort claims pending in the United States District Court, Southern District of New York, brought by clean-up workers after the September 11th terrorist attacks.  Act as one of a handful of defense liaison counsel tasked with managing the litigation (including well over 1,000 claims) on behalf of the defense group.   
Handle litigation and counsel clients related to a variety of contractual and business tort disputes, including claims related to alter ego/piercing the corporate veil.
Successfully prosecuted proceeding in state court in Albany on behalf of major company challenging order of New York Public Service Commission related to disposition of corporate assets.
Handle client litigation/arbitrations and counseling related to stock purchase and asset sale agreements (particularly indemnification and assumption of liabilities) in various industries.
Advise on litigation/arbitration related to gas royalty disputes, including complex class actions and related proceedings.
Handle litigation/counseling in mineral rights disputes.
Representation of generating company related to environmental compliance and permitting issues for power generating stations, including complex issues under the federal Clean Water Act and defense of citizens’ suit claims. 







Selected for inclusion in BTI Consulting Group’s 2016 “Client Service All Stars” in the Commercial Litigation Category. In the annual report, BTI recognizes lawyers for client service excellence based on unprompted feedback from leading corporate decision makers at Fortune 1,000 companies. 
Selected for inclusion in The Best Lawyers in America, Mass Tort Litigation, Class Action-Defendants Woodward/White, Inc., 2006-2017
Named to "New York Super Lawyers," Class Action/Mass Torts, Business Litigation, Energy & Natural Resources, Super Lawyers, Thomson Reuters, 2006-2009, 2011-2016









						Co-moderator, "View From the Bench: Judges Speak Out on Current Litigation Trends, Successful Plaintiff Claims and Defense Strategies,"  15th National Advanced Forum on Asbestos Claims & Litigation, American Conference Institute, October 7-8, 2013
					

						Moderator, "The Regulatory State: How The EPA and Federal Agencies Are Boxing In and With Industry," McGuireWoods LLP and McGuireWoods Consulting LLC 11th Annual Environmental & Energy Issues Symposium, April 6, 2011
					

						Presenter, "Medicare Reporting Issues in the Asbestos Litigation," New York Asbestos Litigation Conference, February 23, 2010
					

						Presenter, "National Coordinating Counsel’s Update on U.S. Asbestos Litigation and Key U.S. Jurisdictions," C5 6th International Asbestos Claims and Liabilities Conference, January 28, 2010
					

						Presenter, "U.S. Asbestos Litigation: A National Coordinating Counsel's Perspective on Developments in Key Jurisdiction," C5 5th International Asbestos Claims and Liabilities Conference, January 2009
					

						Speaker, "Asbestos Litigation,"  Mealey’s 3rd Annual International Asbestos Conference Global Litigation Update, October 17-18, 2007
					

						Speaker, "The Practical Art of Settling Claims: Key Tips and Techniques from the Trenches,"  C5's 3rd International Asbestos Claims and Liabilities: The Practical Guide to Litigating, Settling and Managing Asbestos Claims, January 25-26, 2007
					






















