Overview


Honors









PRINT










Philip — former managing partner of the firm’s New York office for over 8 years — is a nationally recognized litigator with extensive mass torts (asbestos), products liability and commercial litigation experience.  Among his many honors, Phil has been recognized for his client service excellence for commercial litigation as a BTI Client Service All-Star for 2016. With a unique depth of experience, he litigates in a wide range of high-profile industries and business sectors in Federal and State Courts and arbitration/mediation proceedings throughout the United States, including mass torts and product liability, complex commercial litigation and energy. He has acted for several years as national counsel for Fortune 300 companies in asbestos litigation pending throughout the United States and addressed various issues associated with that litigation (including indemnification disputes and insurance coverage issues).
During his career, Phil's experience derives from acting as lead counsel in high-profile mass tort and complex commercial cases. He acted as a defense liaison counsel in litigation pending in the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York brought by clean-up workers alleging injuries related to their work in buildings after the September 11th terrorist attacks. He has also acted for many years as a liaison counsel for the New York City Asbestos Litigation (NYCAL) medical defense group, a group which oversees medical and other major issues faced by defendants in the NYCAL. 






